Package: BJM
Title: Backward Joint Model for Dynamic Prediction Using Multivariate Longitudinal and Competing Risk Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Wenhao", "li", email = "liwh0904@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5050-443X"))
           )
Maintainer: Wenhao Li <wl68@rice.edu>
Description: This package provides tools for fitting joint models that integrate longitudinal and time-to-event data, aimed at enabling dynamic prediction. It supports the analysis of multiple longitudinal outcomes alongside various event times, including both time-to-event data and scenarios involving competing risks. This functionality allows for comprehensive modeling of complex datasets where longitudinal and survival processes are interconnected.
